ENTRY            A0229   20251205   20260317   20260317       A129
SUBENT        A0229001   20251205   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                  8         19
TITLE      The production of neutron-rich nuclides in the
           heavy-element region via He-3 induced reactions.
AUTHOR     (Y.Y.Chu,M.L.Zhou)
REFERENCE  (J,IRE,30,1149,1983)
INSTITUTE  (1USABNL,3CPRSIU)
FACILITY   (ISOCY,1USABNL)
METHOD     (CHSEP,BCINT,SITA)  Additional information is absent.
ADD-RES    32 different cross sections for the 238U(He3,x)Ac-233
           at a single incident energy. The authors give
           calculated apparent cross sections for Ac-233 based on
           the observed Th-233 activities and different values
           assumed for the half-life of Ac-233.
HISTORY    (19841012C)
           (19861204U)
           (20160317A) SD:Updated to new date formats, lower case.
           Corrections in REACTION code in Subents 002-004.RAD-DET
           deleted from Subents (info presented in DECAY-DATA).
           (20251205A) SD: Corrections in all Subents. Subent 004
           deleted (information moved to ADD-RES).
ENDBIB              19
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           22
SUBENT        A0229002   20251205   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                  7         18
REACTION   (92-U-238(HE3,X)90-TH-233,,SIG,,(A))
DETECTOR   (GELI) Ge(Li) detector (50 cm3 in size with FWHM of
           2.0 keV at 1332 keV)
SAMPLE     Uranium oxide of two different thicknesses and
           uranium foil (thickness - 0.0015 inch) were
           used in this measurement.
DECAY-DATA (90-TH-233,22.2MIN,DG,162.0,0.0031,
                              DG,169.0,0.0034,
                              DG,459.4,0.0135,
                              DG,670.1,0.0065)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The errors of the cross sections reflect the
           larger quantity of either the combination of counting
           statistics, detector efficiency and chemical yield
           uncertainties or the standard deviation of the
           individual measurements from the mean.
STATUS     (TABLE,,Y.Y.Chu+,J,IRE,30,1149,1983) Tbl. 2
HISTORY    (20160317A) SD: SF3=2A -> X in REACTION code.
           (20251205U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB              18
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 3          3
EN         DATA       DATA-ERR
MEV        MICRO-B    MICRO-B
   46.3        1.3        0.2
   53.0        3.8        0.5
   59.6        6.3        0.6
ENDDATA              5
ENDSUBENT           28
SUBENT        A0229003   20251205   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                  7         16
REACTION   (92-U-238(HE3,X)90-TH-231,,SIG,,(A))
DETECTOR   (GELI) Ge(Li) detector (50 cm3 in size with FWHM of
           2.0 keV at 1332 keV)
SAMPLE     Uranium oxide of two different thicknesses and
           uranium foil (thickness - 0.0015 inch) were
           used in this measurement.
DECAY-DATA (90-TH-231,25.5HR,DG,84.5,0.065,
                             DG,163.0,0.0016)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The errors of the cross sections reflect the
           larger quantity of either the combination of counting
           statistics, detector efficiency and chemical yield
           uncertainties or the standard deviation of the
           individual measurements from the mean.
STATUS     (TABLE,,Y.Y.Chu+,J,IRE,30,1149,1983) Tbl. 2
HISTORY    (20160317A) SD: SF3=2N+2A -> X in REACTION code.
           (20251205U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB              16
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 3          3
EN         DATA       DATA-ERR
MEV        MICRO-B    MICRO-B
   46.3        2.8        0.3
   53.0       10.6        1.1
   59.6       16.2        2.0
ENDDATA              5
ENDSUBENT           26
